devdoc.details: It contains some common internal functions and variables for the consensus contracts.

addSigner(address).details: The sender must be the owner.It throws a require error if the sender is not the owner.

addSigners(address[]).details: The sender must be the owner.It throws a require error if the sender is not the owner.

initialize(address).details: Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.

initialize(address,address,address).details: The caller address must be the loans contract for LoanTermsConsensus, and the lenders contract for InterestConsensus.

params.aCallerAddress: the contract that will call it.

initialized().return: true if contract is initialized. Otherwise it returns false.

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

isSigner(address).return: true if account is a signer. Otherwise it returns false.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeSigner(address).details: The sender must be the owner.It throws a require error if the sender is not the owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * > Note: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

addSigner(address).notice: It adds a new account as a signer.

addSigners(address[]).notice: It adds a list of account as signers.

initialized().notice: Gets if the contract is initialized.
